question:We buy one kilo of tomatoes which costs one euro and forty cents; and we pay with a five euro bill. How much change do we get back? 
answers:four euros and fifty cents,three euros and sixty cents,two euros and sixty cents,sixty cents
correctAnswer:three euros and sixty cents

question:We buy a box of sweets which costs eight euro and sixty cents; and we pay with a ten euro bill. How much change do we get back? 
answers:one euro and five cents,two euros and ninety cents,one euro and forty cents,forty cents
correctAnswer:one euro and forty cents
